  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 9 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 13 high, 7 medium, 19 normal. Key bases needing attention include Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and Larnaca (LCA/LCLK); plus 10 other bases. 7 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, thunderstorm / convective risk and fog / freezing fog  — most notably around Tuzla (TZL/LQTZ), Varna (VAR/LBWN) and David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO). Network hotspots: Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Tenerife Sur (TFS/GCTS), Mohammed V (CMN/GMMN), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH) and 4 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and thunderstorm / convective risk. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR), Bodensee Airport Friedrichshafen (FDH/EDNY), Glasgow (GLA/EGPF) and 9 others.",
